items.htmlSnippet:
Cross-country skiing is a form of skiing where skiers rely on their own locomotion
to move across snow-covered terrain, rather than using ski lifts or other forms of
assistance. Cross-country skiing is widely practised as a sport and recreational
activity; however, some still use it as a means of transportation.
